UID:occ-494@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Eric Idle's Tony-winning Arthurian spoof — killer rabbits\, 
 taunting Frenchmen\, coconut-shell hoofbeats — in a national touring pro
 duction.\n\nKing Arthur recruits his knights and quests for the Grail past
  killer rabbits\, taunting French soldiers\, the Knights Who Say Ni\, and 
 a Lady of the Lake who resents her lack of stage time. Eric Idle adapted t
 he Pythons' 1975 Holy Grail film into a musical\, writing the songs with J
 ohn Du Prez\, including "Always Look on the Bright Side of Life." The orig
 inal 2005 Broadway production won three Tony Awards\, Best Musical among t
 hem. This is a national touring production.
