SUMMARY:Little Shop
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260726T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260726T163000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-823@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Menken and Ashman's doo-wop horror comedy about a skid-row flo
 rist and the plant that drinks blood.\n\nAlan Menken and Howard Ashman's 1
 982 horror-comedy musical. Seymour Krelborn\, a meek clerk in a failing sk
 id-row flower shop\, finds a strange plant after a solar eclipse and names
  it Audrey II\, after the co-worker he loves. The plant turns out to run o
 n human blood\, and as it grows\, Seymour's fortunes and its appetite grow
  together. The score works in early-sixties rock and roll\, doo-wop\, and 
 Motown. Jared Wright and Katherine Coyne direct for Southside Theatre Guil
 d\, Metro Atlanta's oldest all-volunteer community theatre. Runs through A
 ugust 2.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203547Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/877/1785090600000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Great American Trailer Park Musical
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260726T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260726T173000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1413@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Nehls and Kelso's trashy\, big-hearted comedy of adultery\, ag
 oraphobia\, and hurricanes at a Florida trailer park.\n\nDavid Nehls and B
 etsy Kelso's musical comedy\, an Off-Broadway hit in 2005\, set at Armadil
 lo Acres trailer park in Starke\, Florida. Jeannie hasn't stepped outside 
 her trailer in twenty years\; her tollbooth-collector husband Norbert is l
 osing patience\; and Pippi\, a stripper hiding out from a marker-huffing e
 x with a gun named Bertha\, has just moved in next door. The affair that f
 ollows kicks up a storm in more ways than one. From New Depot Players\, th
 e Conyers community theatre.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203541Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/thenewdepotplayers/5082/event/1473895
END:VEVENT
