BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:H.M.S. Pinafore
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T220000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1134@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Gilbert and Sullivan's 1878 comic opera: a captain's daughter\
 , a common sailor\, and a shipload of class satire.\n\nGilbert and Sulliva
 n's first international hit\, from 1878. Aboard a Royal Navy warship\, the
  captain's daughter Josephine loves Ralph Rackstraw\, a lowly sailor\, whi
 le her father has promised her to Sir Joseph Porter\, a First Lord of the 
 Admiralty who rose to run the Navy without ever going to sea. Cue elopemen
 t plans\, a chorus of sisters\, cousins\, and aunts\, and a late revelatio
 n that turns the whole ship upside down. From the Front Porch Players\, a 
 Clayton County community theatre\; runs through August 16.
GEO:33.5144767;-84.3301925
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203536Z
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Church of Jonesboro\, 1842 Lake Jodeco Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://search.seatyourself.biz/webstore/accounts/thefrontporchplayers
 /buy-tix?landingMessageSeen=true
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street (2026)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T223000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-680@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Sondheim's 1979 revenge musical: a wronged barber\, a corrupt 
 judge\, and Mrs. Lovett's suspiciously well-stocked pie shop.\n\nStephen S
 ondheim and Hugh Wheeler's 1979 musical thriller\, based on Christopher Bo
 nd's play. Benjamin Barker returns from wrongful exile as Sweeney Todd\, r
 eopens his barbershop above Mrs. Lovett's failing pie shop\, and sharpens 
 his razors for the judge who destroyed his family. His customers\, meanwhi
 le\, start finding their way into the pies. Charlie Miller directs for Ons
 tage Atlanta\; runs through August 30.
GEO:33.7932167;-84.2681503
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203541Z
LOCATION:OnStage Atlanta\, 3041 N Decatur Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/onstageatlanta/612/event/1436128
END:VEVENT
