SUMMARY:Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street (2026)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T173000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-687@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Sondheim's 1979 revenge musical: a wronged barber\, a corrupt 
 judge\, and Mrs. Lovett's suspiciously well-stocked pie shop.\n\nStephen S
 ondheim and Hugh Wheeler's 1979 musical thriller\, based on Christopher Bo
 nd's play. Benjamin Barker returns from wrongful exile as Sweeney Todd\, r
 eopens his barbershop above Mrs. Lovett's failing pie shop\, and sharpens 
 his razors for the judge who destroyed his family. His customers\, meanwhi
 le\, start finding their way into the pies. Charlie Miller directs for Ons
 tage Atlanta\; runs through August 30.
GEO:33.7932167;-84.2681503
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203541Z
LOCATION:OnStage Atlanta\, 3041 N Decatur Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/onstageatlanta/612/event/1436134
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:All Shook Up
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T223000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-643@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Elvis jukebox musical: a leather-clad roustabout shakes up
  a buttoned-down 1955 town\, Twelfth Night style.\n\nA jukebox musical bui
 lt on the Elvis Presley songbook\, with a book by Joe DiPietro (Memphis) t
 hat borrows its plot from Twelfth Night. In the summer of 1955\, a guitar-
 playing roustabout roars into a town so square its mayor enforces a Decenc
 y Act against loud music\, public necking\, and tight pants. A lovestruck 
 young mechanic named Natalie glues on a beard to get closer to him\, and t
 he romantic entanglements multiply from there\, set to "Jailhouse Rock\," 
 "Hound Dog\," and "Can't Help Falling in Love." From Marietta Theatre Comp
 any\; the show premiered on Broadway in 2005.
GEO:33.9521247;-84.5505287
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203539Z
LOCATION:Marietta's Theatre on the Square\, 11 Whitlock Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/mariettatheatre/5266/event/1444893
END:VEVENT
