BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cotton Patch Gospel: Season 50 Return Engagement
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261017T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261017T163000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-967@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Matthew's Gospel retold in small-town Georgia with Harry Chapi
 n's bluegrass score\, back for Theatrical Outfit's 50th season.\n\nTom Key
  and Russell Treyz's musical transplants the Gospel of Matthew to rural Ge
 orgia\, where Jesus is born in Gainesville and the storytelling runs on ba
 njo and fiddle. The bluegrass score is by Harry Chapin\, his final work be
 fore his death in 1981\, and the show draws on Clarence Jordan's homespun 
 Cotton Patch translations of the New Testament. It returns as a special en
 gagement in Theatrical Outfit's 50th anniversary season\, with performance
 s through October 18.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203548Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
