  family becomes true-crime podcast fodder.\n\nA world-premiere coming-of-a
 ge musical written by Jacob Ryan Smith and Caroline Pernick\, from Allianc
 e Theatre. Seventeen-year-old Chris\, reeling from her father's arrest\, l
 ands with the estranged mother and stepfather she barely knows\, until a h
 it true-crime podcast drags the family's buried past into public view. The
  folk-pop score draws on the stories of relatives left behind by infamous 
 killers\, and on an industry that has grown to 250 million listeners. Tina
 she Kajese-Bolden directs\; the show won the first Open Jar Broadway Shark
  Tank and runs through November 15.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203526Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164244/164517
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ride the Cyclone
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T163000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1382@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Six choir kids die on a roller coaster and compete in song for
  one shot back at life.\n\nJacob Richmond and Brooke Maxwell's cult dark-c
 omedy musical: six teenagers from a small-town Canadian chamber choir peri
 sh on a faulty coaster and wake in limbo\, where a mechanical fortune tell
 er offers exactly one of them a return to life. Each teen pleads their cas
 e in song\, from autotuned gangsta rap to a torchy French lament. The show
  has local roots of a sort — its 2019 Alliance Theatre run supplied the 
 cast for the world premiere recording. A community production from the Hen
 ry Players.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203538Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/ride-the-cyclone-tickets-271694
END:VEVENT
