BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Great American Trailer Park Musical
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T173000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1212@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Nehls and Kelso's raunchy comedy of a stripper on the run and 
 one very stuck marriage in a Florida trailer park.\n\nDavid Nehls and Bets
 y Kelso's Off-Broadway comedy set in Armadillo Acres\, a trailer park in S
 tarke\, Florida. Jeannie hasn't left her trailer since her son was abducte
 d two decades ago\; her tollbooth-collector husband Norbert hopes annivers
 ary Ice Capades tickets will finally coax her out. Then Pippi\, a stripper
  fleeing a marker-sniffing ex-boyfriend\, moves in and complicates everyth
 ing. From Pumphouse Players.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203543Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-great-american-trailer-park-musical-t
 ickets-1989768581390
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Shop of Horrors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T193000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1640@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Menken and Ashman's doo-wop horror comedy: a skid row florist\
 , a bloodthirsty plant\, and a Faustian bargain.\n\nThe 1982 horror-comedy
  musical from Alan Menken and Howard Ashman\, the songwriting team that la
 ter gave Disney The Little Mermaid. Meek flower-shop clerk Seymour discove
 rs a strange plant that turns his fortunes around\, but Audrey II has a ta
 ste for blood and an appetite that keeps growing. The score runs on early-
 '60s rock and roll\, doo-wop\, and Motown\, with a girl-group trio of stre
 et urchins as Greek chorus. Presented by Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203547Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825829/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Notebook
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270413T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270413T220000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1737@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Broadway musical of Nicholas Sparks's tearjerker romance\,
  with songs by Ingrid Michaelson\, on national tour.\n\nNicholas Sparks's 
 1996 novel — already one of the highest-grossing romantic film dramas ev
 er adapted — reworked as a Broadway musical\, with a score by singer-son
 gwriter Ingrid Michaelson and a script by playwright Bekah Brunstetter. Al
 lie and Noah come from different worlds and spend a lifetime finding their
  way back to each other\; the musical splits each role among three actors 
 playing them at different ages. A national touring production\, following 
 the show's 2024 Broadway run.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203536Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=NOT&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
