BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Last Five Years
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270416T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270416T213000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1140@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Jason Robert Brown's two-person musical: her story told backwa
 rd\, his forward\, crossing once on their wedding day.\n\nJason Robert Bro
 wn's song-cycle musical traces five years between Jamie\, a novelist whose
  career takes off fast\, and Cathy\, an actress whose career won't. The tr
 ick is the structure: Cathy tells her story in reverse\, starting at the m
 arriage's end\, while Jamie moves forward from the first date\, and the tw
 o timelines meet only once\, at the wedding. Brown wrote it after his own 
 divorce\, and the score ranges from klezmer to pop ballad. Presented by Ju
 nction Playhouse.
GEO:33.4739853;-84.5085251
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203538Z
LOCATION:Shipyard at Trilith\, 125 Shepperton Wy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/the-junction-playhouse-presents-
 the-last-five-years
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Something Rotten
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270416T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270416T213000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1396@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Two Renaissance playwright brothers scheme to out-write Shakes
 peare by inventing the world's first musical.\n\nThe 2015 Broadway comedy 
 by Karey and Wayne Kirkpatrick with John O'Farrell\, set in 1595: brothers
  Nick and Nigel Bottom run a theatre troupe stuck in the shadow of a rock-
 star Shakespeare. Desperate for an edge\, Nick pays a soothsayer to glimps
 e the future of theatre and learns it involves people bursting into song m
 id-scene. The score is wall-to-wall musical-theatre in-jokes\; the show ea
 rned ten Tony nominations. From the Henry Players community theatre compan
 y.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203538Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/something-rotten-tickets-269298
END:VEVENT
