BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Roald Dahl's Matilda\, the Musical
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T213000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1301@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Dahl's telekinetic bookworm takes on the fearsome Miss Trunchb
 ull\, with songs by Tim Minchin.\n\nDennis Kelly and Tim Minchin's musical
  adaptation of Roald Dahl's novel about Matilda Wormwood\, a brilliant lit
 tle girl saddled with crooked parents and a child-hating headmistress who 
 invents punishments for sport. Matilda fights back with wit\, a fierce lov
 e of books\, and a psychokinetic trick or two\, finding an ally in her gen
 tle teacher Miss Honey. First staged by the Royal Shakespeare Company\, th
 e show won a record seven Olivier Awards in 2012. This production comes fr
 om Arcadia Theater\, the community company continuing three decades of the
 atre-making in its space.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203529Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/roald-dahl-s-matilda-the-musical-tickets-2
 79870
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Hunchback of Notre Dame
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T213000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-1402@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Disney's stage musical of Hugo's bell-ringer tale\, with the M
 enken and Schwartz score\, from the Henry Players.\n\nThe stage musical dr
 awn from Disney's 1996 animated film\, itself adapted from Victor Hugo's 1
 831 Gothic novel. Quasimodo\, the bell-ringer hidden away in Notre Dame's 
 tower\, longs for the world beyond the cathedral walls and finds a friend 
 in Esmeralda\, a Romani woman who stands up to his cruel guardian\, Judge 
 Frollo. The Alan Menken and Stephen Schwartz score is darker and more seri
 ous than most of the Disney songbook. A volunteer community production fro
 m the Henry Players.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203538Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/the-hunchback-of-notre-dame-tickets-269295
END:VEVENT
