BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hairspray
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270722T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270722T223000
DTSTAMP:20260720T203550Z
UID:occ-852@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The 2002 Tony-winning musical: a big-haired Baltimore teen dan
 ces her way onto TV and into the civil rights fight.\n\nBaltimore\, 1962: 
 Tracy Turnblad\, big of hair and bigger of heart\, wins a spot on a local 
 TV dance show and starts campaigning to integrate it. Marc Shaiman and Sco
 tt Wittman's score runs on 1960s dance-party pop and rhythm and blues\, ad
 apted from John Waters's 1988 film\; the Broadway production took eight To
 ny Awards\, including Best Musical. Presented by Southside Theatre Guild\,
  an all-volunteer community theatre running since 1973.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T203547Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/1031/1816300800000
END:VEVENT
